##Download (a subset of) ATAC-seq peak counts in the hippocampus upon stress (already in SummarizedExperiment format): #○ https://ethz-ins.org/content/mouse_mm38_hippocampus.peakCounts.SE.rds #○(the data is from the mouse ensembl GRCm38 genome – you should already have the genome, e.g. from week 6)

##Using this object, perform a chromVAR motif analysis, and run 2 differential motif accessibility analyses, respectively: #○ comparing stressed (denoted ‘FSS’ – forced swim stress) and control animals #○ comparing male and female animals

##For each analysis, report the top most significant motifs, plot a heatmap of the normalized accessibility scores across the samples for those motifs, and write a short paragraph interpreting the results.

suppressPackageStartupMessages({
  library(epiwraps)
  library(motifmatchr)
  library(MotifDb)
  library(AnnotationHub)
  library(universalmotif)
  library(ggplot2)
  library(SummarizedExperiment) # data structure
  library(sechm) # for plotting heatmaps from a SummrizedExperiment
  library(BiocParallel) # for multithreading
  library(chromVAR) # for motif accessibility estimation
  library(limma) # for statistical analysis
})
## Warning: package 'GenomeInfoDb' was built under R version 4.3.3
## Warning: package 'Biostrings' was built under R version 4.3.3
## See system.file("LICENSE", package="MotifDb") for use restrictions.
## Warning: package 'AnnotationHub' was built under R version 4.3.3
#install.packages("Matrix", version="1.6.3")
# to control multithreading, unix users can use:
register(MulticoreParam(4))

Download the data

options(timeout=6000)
dir.create("peak")
## Warning in dir.create("peak"): 'peak' already exists
download.file("https://ethz-ins.org/content/mouse_mm38_hippocampus.peakCounts.SE.rds", destfile = "peak/ATAC_Peaks.rds", mode = "wb")
peak <- readRDS("peak/ATAC_Peaks.rds")

# get mouse genome
dir.create("genome")
## Warning in dir.create("genome"): 'genome' already exists
ah <- AnnotationHub()
genome <- ah[["AH68356"]]
## loading from cache
## require("rtracklayer")
# we'll load it into memory:
genome_seqs <- import(genome)
Biostrings::writeXStringSet(genome_seqs, "genome.fa")
# preparing the genome sequence file (here just using a subset)
genome_fa <- Rsamtools::FaFile("genome.fa")

Interpretation

CTRL - FSS:

-VolcanoPlot:The 6 most significant motifs –> significant difference of these motifs in stressed animals compared to the same ones in controls. And based on logFC (which is positive for all the top 10) the accessabilty of the motif in FSS animals is higher compared to control animals.

-Heatmap: gives us z-score of significant motifs for the two different conditions: CTRL and FSS –> the stressed animals show a higher z-score –> higher acessability for the listed motifs in stressed animals; Only one column from the stressed condition shows no difference in the z-score for any of the motifs (my interpretation: this one columne is one animal that did not behave as expected)

Female - Male:

-VolcanoPlot: #The 6 most significant motifs -> significant difference of these motifs in males compared to the same ones in females. And based on logFC (which is negative for all the top 10) the accessabilty of the motif in males is lower compared to females

-Heatmap: #gives us z-score of different motifs for male vs female and for the two conditions (CTRL - FSS) –> males show a higher z-score than females –> higher acessability for the listed motifs in males
